    "If we go from full intuitionistic modal frames to general intuitionistic modal frames for L ′ (Φ, I), then P is any set of downsets closed under ∩, ⊃, ■ i, and ∪.",
    "These frames are clearly also partial-state frames.",
    "(The above treatment of ∨ ○, as in intuitionistic Kripke semantics [Kripke, 1965], makes the forcing clauses for intuitionistic and classical disjunction different (recall Fact 2.4).",
